Comment: This game shows how much chess you can learn in a couple months of practice and hard work. This game ends in 28 moves with checkmate. enjoy!
Back to Back king pawn pushes.
I bring out my knight to f3 as usual.
black knight to c6
An opening I have been doing alot of lately and it works for me. This move opens up for the queen to check the king and also prepares for a pawn push to either d3 or d4 but usually d4.
Black moves pawn to d5 which throws me off for a second because I am not used to seeing that move.
I respond with pawn to d3
Black takes on e4
I retake on d4
This is not my favorite transaction but I did not mind this time. Queen takes Queen
King takes Queen.
Black bishop to g4 attacking my knight.
I do the same on the opposite side.
Black bishop takes my knight.
I retake.
Black moves pawn to a6 attacking my bishop.
I take his knight as well keeping it even.
Black retakes.
I prepare to develope my pieces by moving knight to d2.
Black does the same by moving bishop to c5 attacking pawn on f2.
